            "text": "Initial assessment: The pulp chamber was reentered and irrigated with saline, followed by the placement of a nonsetting calcium hydroxide material and a double sealing of the access cavity with Cavit™ 3M and glass ionomer cement (GIC) Riva Self Cure™ SDI. Two weeks later, the tooth was reassessed, irrigated with 1.5% sodium hypochlorite (NaOCI), followed by irrigation with sterile water, and filled using EndoSequence material under a dental operating microscope. The root canal was later obturated with thermoplasticised gutta-perca using the Obtura III Max System."
